column5: Got out on the St. Mary's this evening for atlantics.  Fishing was real slow until just before dark.  The fish started herding smelt up to the surface and cutting through them like whales through schools of salmon right near the boat.  It was very cool to see.  A few fish caught, a few missed.  Fish were taken on spoons and jigs. No pics unfortunately.
No pics huh. I thought maybe that was one of you guys I saw out there snapping pics as you were releasing one. I wanted to fish, but I was only out for a boat ride
no cam unfortunately.  there was tons of fish right up at the booms tonight though that's for sure.
